title: Grete Waitz Bislett
content: Honoring long distance runner Grete Waitz of Oslo, Norway. The statue was originally placed the Grete Waitz plass before being moved to the north Bislett Stadium entrance.

title: Dronning Maud Statue
content: The statue of Queen Maud stands at the entrance of the Queen Park, and was made by Ada Madsen (1917-2009). It was unveiled by King Olav V in 1959.

title: Kronprinsesse Märtha Statue
content: The statue of Crown Princess Märtha stands at Gardevaktstuen on the north side of the castle and was made by Kirsten Kokkin (1951-). It was a gift from the Storting on the occasion of King Harald's 70th anniversary and was unveiled by him on 21 February 2007. A similar statue is on the lawn in front of the ambassador's residence in Washington DC - a tribute to the Crown Princess's efforts for Norway in the United States under 2. World War.

title: Camilla Collett / I storm
content: The monument is called "I storm". An aging Camilla Collett stands alone in the cold wind, and shruggs the shawl closer to her shoulders. The monument is cast in bronze and was unveiled in 1911.
